Success Nwogu and Enyioha Opara A former Vice-President, Atiku Abubakar, on Friday solicited help for the victims of the fire at the Internally Displaced Persons camp in Ngala, Borno State. Mr Garba Shehu, media aide to the President, Major-General Muhammadu Buhari (retd), had in a statement said about 14 persons were killed in the fire incident. Atiku in his verified personal twitter handle@atiku said the fire outbreak was sad. He said, “The loss of over a dozen lives in a fire at the IDP camp in Ngala, Borno State, leaving scores injured and hundreds homeless makes me sad. “I hope that help will be expedited for the injured and homeless.” Meanwhile, the International Federation of Women Lawyers, Niger State chapter, has visited the Internally Displaced Persons at Kuta in the Shiroro Local Government Area of the state. During the visit, the group, led by its Chairperson, Christy Barau, presented relief materials to the inmates and victims of bandits’ attacks in Shiroro and its environs. Copyright PUNCH.
